173.—To the Archdeacon of Barnstaple.-—The Bishop had been informed

that the Cemetery of the Church of BARNSTAPLE had been polluted by bloodshed, during a, fight between two of the parishiouers, Ralph Symon and Richard lVarnes. The Archdeacon was to investigate the case ; and, if he found that the said Cemetery had been polluted as alleged, he was

to forbid all interments therein until it should have been reconciled.— Dated at Faringdon (Hants), 23 Dec.
